                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>Actually, I never shut up, really. I've always had so much to say, and I've always been intent on saying it. Sure, I would love to talk like James Bond or Tom Cruise, somebody suave and effortlessly effective. But, so what?</p>
<p>Although I guess theoretically I live in a world where 99 percent of people do something that I can't, I could care less. So, I asked myself Sunday night: Am I disabled? What a dumb question, I thought.</p>
<p>Nick Christie is a Trinity senior and associate sports editor of The Chronicle.</p>
